Note about Spring 6 and XML

These XML files are fully compatible with Spring Framework 6.x, Jakarta Servlet 6.0, Tomcat 10.1, and JDK 21.
One thing to be aware of is that
<welcome-file>login</welcome-file> 
may not invoke a Spring controller consistently because welcome files are handled by the servlet container. 
A more reliable approach is to use a simple index.jsp that redirects to /login, or map / in your LoginController:
@GetMapping("/")
public String home() {
    return "redirect:/login";
}
This ensures that requests always go through Spring MVC before reaching your controllers.







